<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="assessments">
  <title>Assessments</title>
  <p>
    This course will have in-class, written assessments.
    You may not use the text, your notes, or any devices.
  </p>
  <p>
    Each assessment will contain problems corresponding to one or more standards.
    The standards are scored <em>independently</em> using the scale in the <xref ref="scoring" text="title"/> section.
    To master a standard, you must earn a score of <alert>M</alert> on <alert>all</alert> of the problems that go with the standard.
  </p>

  <assemblage>
    <title>Reassessment</title>
    <p>
      There are scheduled Reassessment days for this course (see the <xref ref="schedule" text="title"/>) where you will be given problems for <em>every</em> standard that you have <em>not yet mastered</em>.
      You may attempt as many standards as time allows.
    </p>
  </assemblage>
</subsection>
